<simpara><emphasis role="strong">Industry Foundation Classes</emphasis>
The most widely used architecture and engineering standard for representing and exchanging data about buildings and their components is the IFC (Industry Foundation Classes) <link linkend="NR-IFC">[4]</link>. IFC represents logical building structures and their accompanying properties (attributes) along with 2D and 3D geometry. IFC can also represent utilities components as building services, but generally focuses on buildings themselves rather than general city infrastructure.</simpara>
